heroDescription:
An email service for ~1.8B users handling ~1B incoming emails per day plus outgoing. The hard parts:
      an <span class="hl">SMTP ingress</span> that accepts mail from anyone on the public internet while rejecting terabytes of daily spam;
      a <span class="hl-accent">per-user mailbox store</span> sharded across thousands of machines with search, labels, and conversation threading;
      and <span class="hl-accent">delivery reputation management</span> so your outbound mail doesn't get marked spam by other providers.
      Gmail pioneered "search, don't sort" — replaced folders with labels + full-text search, which changed the email paradigm.
